A South African Airways aircraft is seen at OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - A group of about two hundred South Africans repatriated from the US claim they were stranded for five hours after landing at OR Tambo airport. The group arrived on Monday afternoon as part of the repatriation process amid the coronavirus pandemic. COVID-19: Govt continues to bring South Africans home It's unclear what caused the delay in taking them to the place where they will be quarantined for 14-days. One member of the group spoke to eNCA on condition of anonymity alleging that the Birchwood Hotel where they were to be quarantined terminated its contract with government. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.